Actions.Text: AMEND AND RECOMMIT TO HIGHER EDUCATION

Title: Relates to unprofessional conduct by dentists
Summary: Provides that unprofessional conduct by dentists includes the failure, prior to the initial diagnosis and correction of malpositions of human teeth, to perform an examination, including the review of the patient's most recent diagnostic digital or conventional radiographs or other equivalent bone imaging suitable for orthodontia.
ActClause: AN ACT to amend the education law, in relation to unprofessional dental conduct
